{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D9Ce2r5FbHwEcUinB47buU","type":"tool_result","content":"   870→\n   871→1. **STOP RALPH NOW.** Kill the process. There is nothing left to do. Every additional loop burns ~$2.35 for zero value.\n   872→2. **Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph.** When `sprint.done == sprint.total` and no stories are in-progress, Ralph should exit immediately with a success message. This is the permanent fix.\n   873→3. **Fix the stale-state overwrite bug.** Ralph should read `sprint-state.json` from disk at the start of each loop iteration, not rely on a startup snapshot. Or: make the state file read-only once sprint completes.\n   874→4. **Attribute the `unknown` cost bucket.** $175.76 (23.8% of total) has no story attribution. Likely orchestrator overhead, retro sessions, or Ralph's own loop logic.\n   875→5. **Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom.** Remove from any tracking. $24.35 already wasted.\n   876→\n   877→### Verdict\n   878→\n   879→Sprint: DONE. 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics. Shipped.\n   880→\n   881→Ralph: BROKEN. 44 consecutive no-op sessions. ~$103 burned on the same fix. Combined with unattributed overhead ($175.76) and phantom cost ($24.35), total identifiable waste is ~$303 — 41% of the $738.35 sprint budget.\n   882→\n   883→The retro mechanism cannot stop Ralph. This is the 44th retro saying the same thing. Kill the process manually or add an exit condition. There is no other path.\n   884→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01B7hcdUQ799w7XiBTC6pwmC","session_id":"3901ff66-fcbf-4672-8c7c-fef2613cf9a8","uuid":"49110a5f-0517-499f-9824-b9efd8657fdd","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:54:12.078Z"}
