{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B7hcdUQ799w7XiBTC6pwmC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Session 61 retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md`.\n\nSummary:\n\n- **Sprint:** Complete. 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics. Done since session 30.\n- **This session:** No-op. State corruption fix #45. Same bug, same fix, same retro.\n- **Cost:** $739.95 total, up $1.60 from last session. ~$311 (42%) is identifiable waste -- no-op session churn ($110), unattributed overhead ($177), phantom story ($24).\n- **Root cause:** Ralph has no sprint-complete exit condition and overwrites disk state with a stale in-memory snapshot each loop.\n- **Required action:** Kill Ralph. Then add an exit condition and a status-reversion guard. 45 retros have said this. Nothing short of process termination or code changes will break the loop."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aaa9dd18567ebb88c (use SendMessage with to: 'aaa9dd18567ebb88c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 29035\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 73126</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3901ff66-fcbf-4672-8c7c-fef2613cf9a8","uuid":"8e506d41-9414-42d6-8041-d95a6823d337","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:54:59.897Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run a session retrospective for the current sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --save` to get the cost report, then read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md`.\n\nThis is session 61. It was a NO-OP session — the sprint is 100% complete (74/74 stories, 17/17 epics done). The only work done was fixing state corruption for the 45th time: Ralph's stale in-memory state reverted stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from `done` to `review` and epic-16 from `done` to `backlog`.\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. It documents 45+ consecutive state corruption fixes.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `npx codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis.\n\nProduce a retrospective covering:\n1. **Session summary** — no-op, state corruption fix #45\n2. **Issues analysis** — the recurring state corruption root cause\n3. **Cost analysis** — from cost report, emphasize waste from 45+ no-op sessions\n4. **What went well** — sprint IS complete\n5. **What went wrong** — Ralph won't stop, state corruption loop\n6. **Lessons learned** — Ralph needs a sprint-complete exit condition\n7. **Action items** — stop Ralph, fix state overwrite bug\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md, APPEND to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"aaa9dd18567ebb88c","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Session 61 retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md`.\n\nSummary:\n\n- **Sprint:** Complete. 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics. Done since session 30.\n- **This session:** No-op. State corruption fix #45. Same bug, same fix, same retro.\n- **Cost:** $739.95 total, up $1.60 from last session. ~$311 (42%) is identifiable waste -- no-op session churn ($110), unattributed overhead ($177), phantom story ($24).\n- **Root cause:** Ralph has no sprint-complete exit condition and overwrites disk state with a stale in-memory snapshot each loop.\n- **Required action:** Kill Ralph. Then add an exit condition and a status-reversion guard. 45 retros have said this. Nothing short of process termination or code changes will break the loop."}],"totalDu